	(52,1,'2013-05-03 00:10:28','2013-05-03 00:10:28','<h2>Everyone Has a Smartphone</h2>\r\n<p>Okay, maybe not everyone, but it\'s definitely heading that way! Over 40% of all your website visitors will be using a smartphone or other mobile device. In fact, 10% of all internet users will only be using their phones. This means that users are starting to turn in their desktop and laptops computers for iPhones and Androids.</p>\r\n<p>So what does all of this mean for you? Well, it means two main things. First, you need to make sure your website is mobile friendly. Secondly, layout and content structure is really really really important. Having a mobile friendly website use to be complicated and expensive because it required different version for each device you wanted to support. In 2012, a new kid on the block showed up that changed everything. We\'ll call him Mr. Responsive.</p>\r\n<h2>The New Responsive Mindset</h2>\r\n<p>If you are just getting started with your website than you are already a step ahead. You don\'t really need to rethink the way you have approached your content and layout...</p>','Why Mobile Friendly Matters?','','inherit','open','open','','34-revision-5','','','2013-05-03 00:10:28','2013-05-03 00:10:28','',34,'http://localhost:8888/jeremybasham_finalproject_wp/wordpress/?p=52',0,'revision','',0),
